# Vibe-Log Protocol
- Handoff after Refactoring: After every major architectural change, feature completion, or significant refactor, you MUST execute: npx @edenkollcinaku/vibe-log handoff.

- Long-term Memory: Before starting any new task, read the latest entries in VIBE.md to understand previous decisions and the current "vibe" of the project.

- Confidence Assessment: Respect the confidenceScore field in the ledger; if a previous session has "Low" confidence, verify that logic thoroughly before extending or building upon it.

- Session Conclusion: When finishing a task or when the user indicates the session is ending, always suggest a final handoff to capture the remaining context.